---HEADER---
file:                  tooling/types.py
language:              python
role:                  Cross-subcommand result dataclasses (Finding,
                       Report). Every cmd_* function in the tooling/
                       package returns a Report; findings inside a
                       Report are Finding instances. The orchestrator
                       reads these to format JSON or text output.
layer:                 core
status:                verified
confidence:            high (rationale: authored fresh in this rc and
                       reviewed against the subcommand-return-shape
                       contract in the mainland)
generation-pass:       false
read-reason:           task-driven
last-verified:         v0.3-rc5-2026-05-03
maintained-by:         llm
exports:
  - Finding
  - Report
imports:
  - dataclasses :: dataclass, field
depends-on:
  - llmisland_tooling.py      :: imports Report for dispatcher output
                                  formatting
  - tooling/common.py         :: filesystem helpers; subcommand modules
                                  combine helpers + types from these two
                                  modules
  - (rc6+) tooling/stale.py, propagation.py, rules.py, validate.py
                              :: every subcommand returns a Report
translation-boundary:  none
dynamic-boundary:      false

---SYMBOLS---

SYMBOL: Finding
kind:           class
pure:           true (frozen dataclass)
total:          true
latency-budget: <1ms
effects:
  reads:    none
  mutates:  none (frozen)
  allocs:   one instance per construction
  throws:   never
  async:    false
  io:       none
called-by:
  - rc6 stale.py       :: emits findings on staleness / decay
  - rc7 propagation.py :: emits findings on cascade state issues
  - rc8 validate.py    :: emits findings during validation
calls:
  - none
expects:
  - severity is one of {"error", "warning", "info"}
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none yet
  regression: none yet
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    low
fragility-note: N/A

SYMBOL: Report
kind:           class
pure:           true (frozen dataclass)
total:          true
latency-budget: <1ms
effects:
  reads:    none
  mutates:  none (frozen)
  allocs:   one instance per subcommand call
  throws:   never
  async:    false
  io:       none
called-by:
  - every rc6+ subcommand :: returns Report from cmd_*
  - llmisland_tooling.main / _emit :: serializes to JSON or text
calls:
  - none
expects:
  - findings is list[Finding]
  - summary is JSON-serializable
runtime-dependencies:
  - none
tests:
  unit:       none yet
  regression: none yet
  security:   none
business-rule: N/A
fragility:    medium (rationale: contract subcommand-return-shape
                                  references this; field renames break
                                  every subcommand silently)
fragility-note: see contract subcommand-return-shape in mainland. Field
                additions are safe (Tier B); renames or removals are
                Tier C and require updating every subcommand module.

---RISKS---

security:                none
regression-sensitivity:
  - Report field renames cascade to every subcommand module — Tier C
  - severity enum is informal: "error" / "warning" / "info" enforced by
    convention, not by code; rc8 validate.py is the natural place to
    formalize it if needed
platform-sensitivity:    none
config-dependencies:     none

---MEMORY---

ACTIVE-CONSTRAINTS:
  - id: AC-001
    constraint:  Finding and Report are the only cross-subcommand
                 result types. Subcommands MUST NOT define their own
                 result dataclasses.
    established: 2026-05-03
    evidence:    contract subcommand-return-shape in mainland

  - id: AC-002
    constraint:  this module stays free of business logic. Adding
                 helper methods or factory functions here breaks the
                 separation between data shapes (here) and helpers
                 (common.py).
    established: 2026-05-03
    evidence:    inferred-from-design (HD-001)

HISTORICAL-DECISIONS:
  - id: HD-001
    decision:  pull dataclasses out of common.py into types.py
    reason:    common.py.llmisland hit 417 lines initially, over the
               400-line red line (CONTRIBUTING file-size rule). The
               source file had 10 exports; even disciplined SYMBOLS
               entries pushed the island over. Splitting by concern
               (helpers stay; data shapes move) brought both islands
               under the limit and made organization more honest.
               types.py specifically holds NO logic — only frozen
               dataclasses — so future contributors and LLMs have a
               clear separation.
    date:      2026-05-03
    outcome:   stable; this island is well under 200 lines
    evidence:  inferred-from-design (file-size-rule pressure)

SUPERSEDED:
  - none yet
